Description: Slvr Tabby

Spayed Female Exotic Shorthair Cat

Age: 9 YEARS 3 MONTHS

Current Location: King County Pet Adoption Center 21615 64TH AVE S KENT, WA 98032

Hi! My name is Roxy and I am available for adoption.

I was brought in by my previous owner on August 19, 2017 because sometimes I went to the bathroom outside the litter box.

My personality color is BLUE. I am a gentle and loving cat who likes to take things slow. I may get nervous in new situations, so I am looking for a family who understands that I might need some time to warm up. Once I get to know you, I will be a very devoted friend!

I am an affectionate lovebug who would be thrilled to cuddle up with you at home!

I was previously declawed on all four paws. Because I can't protect myself outside, I need to be an indoor-only cat.

A veterinarian has diagnosed or tentatively diagnosed the above-described pet with the following condition(s):

1) House soiling: This cat has a long history of house soiling (primarily urinating). The previous owner attempted to have this problem evaluated at a veterinarian and while the problem would resolve for periods of time, it happened repeatedly. Based on the history, this problem is likely a behavioral problem but we recommend discussing this with your veterinarian to determine if further medical evaluation

2) Heart murmur: During our routine exam, a heart murmur was found. There are currently no signs of heart disease. In order to determine the cause of the heart murmur, a cardiac study called an echocardiogram would need to be performed. Although many animals live normal lives with heart murmurs, it is important to discuss this with your veterinarian.

As a result of these conditions, your pet may need specialized care consisting of any or all of the below. Please note this is not intended to be an exhaustive list.

- Special diet or prescription foods

- Prescription or over-the-counter medicines

- Regular veterinarian visits, which may include blood tests or other monitoring

- Possible surgery or other procedures as determined by your veterinarian

My caregivers have noticed that I do not seem to get along with other cats, so I may do best as the only cat in my new home. This could be why I did not always use my litterbox.

Adoption Fee: $30.00
